The open plan floor plates encourage communication and interaction, essential in a successful enterprise. The campus style floor plate allows a truly connected and integrated working environment.

1000 La Trobe St will be Docklands’ newest building and has been designed, by award winning architect Woods Bagot, with connectivity at its core combining work, life and play seamlessly.

Food-and-beverage facilities, retail services and other amenities will make up the ground-floor tenancy mix, whilst an on-site wellness space and end-of-trip facilities will be offered on the second floor.

The building has a tram stop at the front door and is located within a 5-7 minute walk from Southern Cross Station, it also has fantastic road and highway linkages.
